      "locus": "2.57",
      "sanskrit": "yaḥ muniḥ sarvatra deha-jīvitādiṣv api anabhisneho 'bhisneha-varjitas tat tat prāpya śubhāśubhaṃ tat tat śubhaṃ aśubhaṃ vā labdhvā nābhinandati na dveṣṭi śubhaṃ prāpya na tuṣyati na hṛṣyati, aśubhaṃ ca prāpya na dveṣṭi ity arthaḥ | tasya evaṃ harṣa-viṣāda-varjitasya vivekajā prajñā pratiṣṭhitā bhavati",
      "ourRendering": "That sage who, everywhere — even in body, life and the rest — is without fondness, devoid of attachment, on gaining this or that, good or ill, on obtaining this or that, auspicious or inauspicious, neither rejoices nor reviles — on gaining the auspicious he is not gladdened, does not exult; and on gaining the inauspicious he does not revile — that is the meaning. For such a one, devoid of elation and dejection, the insight born of discrimination stands firm.",
