      "sanskrit": "yatataḥ prayatnaṃ kurvataḥ hi yasmāt kaunteya puruṣasya vipaścitaḥ medhāvino 'pi iti vyavahitena saṃbandhaḥ | indriyāṇi pramāthīni pramathana-śīlāni viṣayābhimukhaṃ hi puruṣaṃ vikṣobhayanti ākulīkurvanti, ākulīkṛtya ca haranti prasabhaṃ prasahya prakāśam eva paśyato viveka-vijñāna-yuktaṃ manaḥ",
      "ourRendering": "Of one striving — making effort — ‘hi’ (for), since; O son of Kuntī, of a man, even of one who is wise, discerning — the construction joining across the intervening words. The senses, ‘pramāthīni’, of churning nature — for they agitate, throw into turmoil, a man turned toward objects, and having thrown him into turmoil they ‘carry off by force’, forcibly, openly indeed, the mind of one who sees, the mind endowed with discriminative knowledge.",
