    {
      "voiceId": "madhusudana",
      "author": "Madhusūdana Sarasvatī",
      "school": "Advaita Vedānta",
      "work": "Gūḍhārtha-dīpikā",
      "locus": "2.68",
      "sanskrit": "hi yasmād evaṃ tasmād iti | sarvaśaḥ sarvāṇi samanaskāni | he mahābāho iti sambodhayan sarva-śatru-nivāraṇa-kṣamatvād indriya-śatru-nivāraṇe 'pi tvaṃ kṣamo 'sīti sūcayati | spaṣṭam anyat | tasyeti siddhasya sādhakasya ca parāmarśaḥ | indriya-saṃyamasya sthita-prajñaṃ prati lakṣaṇatvasya mumukṣuṃ prati prajñā-sādhanatvasya copasaṃharaṇīyatvāt ||68||",
      "ourRendering": "‘hi’ (since) — since it is thus, ‘therefore’. From every side, all of them, together with the mind. Addressing him ‘O mighty-armed’, He hints: since you are able to ward off every foe, you are able also to ward off the foe that is the senses. The rest is clear. ‘Of him’ refers to both the accomplished one and the aspirant, since the senses’ restraint, being for the sthita-prajña a mark and for the seeker of release a means to insight, is to be summed up.",
      "source": "data/sources/sanskrit/vedanta/gretil_bhg4comm_ch2.txt (GRETIL: gretil/1_sanskr/2_epic/mbh/ext/bhg4c02u.htm)"
    },
    {
      "voiceId": "sridhara",
      "author": "Śrīdhara Svāmī",
      "school": "Bhakti / Advaita",
      "work": "Subodhinī",
      "locus": "2.68",
      "sanskrit": "indriya-saṃyamasya sthita-prajñatve sādhanatvaṃ coktam upasaṃharati tasmād iti | sādhanatvopasaṃhāre tasya prajñā pratiṣṭhitā jñātavyety arthaḥ | mahābāho ! iti sambodhayan vairi-nigrahe samarthasya tavātrāpi sāmarthyaṃ bhaved iti sūcayati ||68||",
      "ourRendering": "He sums up that restraint of the senses is, for sthita-prajña-hood, the means, by ‘tasmāt’. In the summing-up of its being the means: his insight is to be known as firm, that is the meaning. Addressing him ‘O mighty-armed’, He hints: as you are able in the subduing of foes, so may your ability be here too.",
      "source": "data/sources/sanskrit/vedanta/gretil_bhg4comm_ch2.txt (GRETIL: gretil/1_sanskr/2_epic/mbh/ext/bhg4c02u.htm)"
    },
    {
      "voiceId": "madhva",
      "author": "Madhva (Ānandatīrtha)",
      "school": "Dvaita Vedānta",
      "work": "Gītā-bhāṣya",
      "locus": "2.68",
      "sanskrit": "tasmāt sarvātmanā nigṛhītendriya eva jñānīti nigamayati – tasmāditi",
      "ourRendering": "He concludes that only one whose senses are restrained in every way is a knower, by ‘tasmāt’.",
      "source": "data/sources/sanskrit/vedanta/madhva_gita_bhasya.txt (srimadhvyasa.wordpress.com, Unicode ed. of Madhva's Gītā-bhāṣya)"
    }
